Vite does **not** support the `import { ReactComponent as ... }` syntax out of the box (that’s a Create React App feature).  
To use your SVG as a component in Vite, you need a plugin like `vite-plugin-svgr`.

**Quick Fix (no plugin):**  
Import the SVG as a URL and use it in an `<img>` tag:

````jsx
// filepath: /home/stick/Code/github.com/StoicaTielemans/BEECA_website/src/pages/footer.jsx
import React from 'react';
import logoUrl from '../assets/logo.svg?url';

function Footer() {
  return (
    <footer className="text-gray-600 body-font">
      <div className="container px-5 py-8 mx-auto flex items-center sm:flex-row flex-col">
        <a className="flex title-font font-medium items-center md:justify-start justify-center text-gray-900">
          <img src={logoUrl} alt="logo" className="w-10 h-10" />
          <span className="ml-3 text-xl">Beeca Technics</span>
        </a>
        {/* ...rest of your code... */}
      </div>
    </footer>
  );
}

export default Footer;
````

**If you want to use SVGs as React components in Vite:**  
1. Install SVGR plugin:
   ```sh
   npm install -D vite-plugin-svgr
   ```
2. Add to your `vite.config.js`:
   ```js
   import svgr from 'vite-plugin-svgr';
   export default {
     plugins: [svgr()],
   };
   ```
3. Then you can use:
   ```js
   import { ReactComponent as Logo } from '../assets/logo.svg';
   ```

But for now, using the `?url` import as above will solve your error and show the logo.
